Rating: 3
I made this recipe when my mother-in-law came to visit. I really enjoyed it. My husband enjoyed the recipe, but prefered Ming Tsai's recipe for Teriaki Salmon. I'm going to combine the two recipes tonight with wild salmon. Ming Tsai's recipe for Teriyaki for two servings is as followings: 1/2 cup low sodium dark soy sauce juice and zest of one orange 1.5 TBS brown sugar 2 garlic cloves, peeled and finely minced 1/2TBS finely minced ginger Bring it all to a boil over high heat, and simmer slowly until reduced by half, about 15 minutes. Remove from heat, stir in 1/2 TBS sesame seeds, and cool. Transfer to a baking dish, add the salmon, turn to coat, and marinate for one hour. I'll then blanch the vegetables, and continue on with this recipe. I'm hopeful my husband (and I) will think that this is the absolute best recipe for salmon.

