Rating: 4
This is a little different from my usual teriyaki recipe which doesn't call for any vinegar; I liked the sweet and sour flavor this version has. It worked well with about half the sugar the recipe calls for, however, and after I'd carelessly added the full amount of soy I tasted the sauce and decided to add more vinegar and some sake to offset the saltiness somewhat. A really nice-looking dish, too; it was a shame to cover up the salmon since it came out looking so great. One family member commented that it would probably be good with tuna as well.

